Mxolisi Mngadi, News24Durban &ndash; Two classrooms at the Hillview Primary School in Reservoir Hills were set alight during a violent service delivery protest on Monday, KwaZulu-Natal police said.- Are you there? Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos.One classroom was destroyed and the other was partially burnt, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said. The protesters blocked roads around the school, including Palmiet Road and Varsity Drive, with burning tyres and rocks. The protest began on Sunday night as people threw stones at passing vehicles. Zwane warned motorists to be careful in the area. No arrests had been made.#sapsKZN #SAPS units monitoring #ProtestAction in Reservoir Hills areas. #MotoristsAlert - &gt; Roads barricaded &amp; reports of stone throwing ME&mdash; SA Police Service (@SAPoliceService) May 8, 2017#sapsKZN #SAPS units monitoring #ProtestAction in Reservoir Hills areas. #MotoristsAlert - &gt; Roads barricaded &amp; reports of stone throwing MEHundreds of protesters have gathered at the intersection of Westdale Crescent and Westdene Crescent in Reservoir hills. pic.twitter.com/aUf8TGuEPj&mdash; Nushera Raisa (@nushera) May 8, 2017Hundreds of protesters have gathered at the intersection of Westdale Crescent and Westdene Crescent in Reservoir hills. pic.twitter.com/aUf8TGuEPj 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.